Class BulkQuay

    Encodable
    public class BulkQuay
extends Quay
    A Bulk Quay is a type of quay specifically designed for the unloading of Bulk Carrier vessels.
    Partially implemented in assignment 1, to be completed in assignment 2

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(Object o)
        Returns true if and only if this BulkQuay is equal to the other given BulkQuay.

        For two BulkQuays to be equal, they must have the same ID, ship docked status (must either both be empty or both be occupied) and same tonnage capacity.

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns the human-readable string representation of this BulkQuay.

        The format of the string to return is 

        BulkQuay id [Ship: imoNumber] - maxTonnage
        Where:
        • id is the ID of this quay
        • imoNumber is the IMO number of the ship docked at this quay, or None if the quay is unoccupied.
        • maxTonnage is the maximum weight in tonnes of this quay.

        For example: 

        BulkQuay 2 [Ship: 2372721] - 120
        Overrides:
        toString in class Quay
        Returns:
        string representation of this quay
        Implemented in assignment 1

      • encode

        public String encode()
        Returns the machine-readable string representation of this BulkQuay.

        The format of the string to return is 

        BulkQuay:id:imoNumber:maxTonnage
        Where:
        • id is the ID of this quay
        • imoNumber is the IMO number of the ship docked at this quay, or None if the quay is unoccupied.
        • maxTonnage is the maximum tonnage this quay can handle
        For example: 
        BulkQuay:3:1258691:120
        or 
        BulkQuay:3:None:120
